{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Two-pass: provisional Integration, kept Integration. The failure is at a module handoff boundary (collector/adapters -> aggregation payload -> summary step), not pure single-function logic. Rejected Unit because behavior text requires cross-module inclusion from \"all three sources.\" Rejected System because no real OS/network/subprocess is required to catch omission; in-process source fakes can expose missing/overwritten sections. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because this behavior checks input assembly before model judgment.","test_description":"Wire real aggregation/report modules with three in-process source fakes returning distinct sentinel fields. Execute collection+assembly and assert the exact payload sent to summary-generation contains all three source sections and values (catching dropped fields, key collisions, or mapper mismatch).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Two-pass: provisional Integration, kept Integration after Integration-brake checks. Failure is resilience across modules (source adapter error propagation -> section renderer fallback). Rejected Unit because behavior spans source call, error mapping, and report composition. Rejected System: \"unavailable\" can be reproduced by a fake adapter raising timeout/503 exceptions, so real network is not strictly required. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness is fallback control flow, not model output quality.","test_description":"Run report generation with two source fakes returning data and one fake raising a realistic unavailability error. Assert process does not abort, output includes normal sections for available sources, and unavailable section contains the required `data unavailable` note.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Two-pass: provisional Agentic, kept Agentic. This is output-quality correctness of the summary itself (faithfulness to key values), which depends on real model behavior and can vary across runs. Rejected Integration because deterministic stubs would always pass and cannot detect hallucination/omission in real generation. Rejected Workflow because the behavior targets one agentic decision (summary generation), not multiple agentic stages in sequence.","test_description":"Call the real summary-generation model on a fixed set of structured inputs with known key values and run repeated trials with acceptance criteria for factual inclusion/consistency (e.g., required metrics/issues/deploy highlights must be present and numerically consistent). Fail on omissions, value drift, or invented facts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.68,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Two-pass: provisional System, kept System. Real external boundaries are central: source APIs plus email delivery/inbox receipt. Rejected Integration because in-process mocks can hide auth, transport, envelope, and provider-format issues that only appear with real HTTP/SMTP/API behavior. Rejected Agentic despite possible summary step because behavior text is delivery outcome (\"reaches ... inbox correctly\"), not model-output quality; the higher level is disqualified by scope of assertion.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled script against test/staging endpoints and a real mailbox sink account. Verify end-to-end: data collected, report composed, email accepted by provider, and message arrives in the configured inbox with expected subject/body structure and attachments/format.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Two-pass: provisional Integration, kept Integration after brake checks. The core failure is orchestration/state handoff across modules: send failure handling -> local persistence -> next-run retry logic. Rejected Unit because it spans multiple components and persisted state. Rejected System because unreachable email can be simulated by send-client error injection, and retry-on-next-run can be validated by invoking two runs with the same local state store; real scheduler/network is not strictly required for this behavior.","test_description":"Use a temp filesystem path with real persistence, configure email client fake to fail on run 1 then succeed on run 2. Assert run 1 writes fallback report file/queue record; run 2 reloads pending report and attempts resend; on success, pending artifact is cleared or marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.67,"System":0.21,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
